theorem isOpen_of_isClosed_and_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP3 : Topology.P3 A) :
    IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  -- First, rewrite `P3` using `closure_eq` for the closed set `A`.
  have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
    simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using hP3
  -- We always have `interior A ⊆ A`.
  have h_subset' : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A := interior_subset
  -- Hence `interior A = A`.
  have h_eq : interior (A : Set X) = A :=
    Set.Subset.antisymm h_subset' h_subset
  -- The interior of any set is open; rewriting with `h_eq` gives the result.
  simpa [h_eq] using isOpen_interior

theorem P2_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P2 (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P2]
  intro x _
  simp [interior_univ, closure_univ]
